criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion criteria:

          -  age 14 to 18 years (inclusive);

          -  literacy in English;

          -  significant substance abuse problems indicated by a score in the problematic range on
             either the AUDIT (4 or above) or the DAST-A (6 or above);

          -  significant mental health problems as indicated by a score in the clinical range on at
             least one subscale of the YSR (T-score 65 or over);

          -  informed consent to participate in study;

          -  participation in regular case management or counselling (at least twice per month)1.

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  history of schizophrenia or other psychotic disorder,

          -  evidence of an organic brain syndrome or severe intellectual disability;

          -  family members who are participating in the family intervention
